  theme_minimal()

Logfold change along with certain and uncertain value

The results highlight how phosphorylation events vary in their certainty and complexity.

This analysis sets the stage for how specific phosphorylation patterns influence gene function and contribute to cellular behavior.

library(readxl)

# Load the data
file_path <- "C://Users//avani//Downloads//Final_Cleaned_Data.xlsx"  # Update with your file path
data <- read_excel(file_path)

# Clean the data for leading/trailing spaces
data$Old_Phos_Positions <- trimws(data$Old_Phos_Positions)

# Function to count genes matching a target pattern
count_genes_with_pattern <- function(pattern) {
  has_pattern <- function(mods) {
    if (is.na(mods)) {
      return(FALSE)  # Return FALSE if there are no values
    }
    return(grepl(pattern, mods))
  }
  genes_with_pattern <- sapply(data$Old_Phos_Positions, has_pattern)
  return(sum(genes_with_pattern))
}

# Define target patterns
patterns <- c(
  "Phospho@\\d+=\\d+;",                           # One certain value
  "Phospho@\\d+=\\d+;Phospho@\\d+=\\d+;",         # Two certain values
  "Phospho@\\d+\\|\\d+;",                         # One uncertain value
  "Phospho@\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+;",                  # Two uncertain values
  "Phospho@\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+;",           # Three uncertain values
  "Phospho@\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+;",    # Four uncertain values
  "Phospho@\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+;",  # Five uncertain values
  "Phospho@\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+;"  # Six uncertain values
)

# Calculate and display totals for each pattern
for (pattern in patterns) {
  total_genes <- count_genes_with_pattern(pattern)
  cat("Total number of genes with pattern", pattern, ":", total_genes, "\n")
}

Bar Graph along with certain and uncertain value

library(readxl)
library(ggplot2)

# Load the data
file_path <- "C://Users//avani//Downloads//Final_Cleaned_Data.xlsx"  # Update with your file path
data <- read_excel(file_path)

# Clean the data for leading/trailing spaces
data$Old_Phos_Positions <- trimws(data$Old_Phos_Positions)

# Function to count genes matching a target pattern
count_genes_with_pattern <- function(pattern) {
  has_pattern <- function(mods) {
    if (is.na(mods)) {
      return(FALSE)  # Return FALSE if there are no values
    }
    return(grepl(pattern, mods))
  }
  genes_with_pattern <- sapply(data$Old_Phos_Positions, has_pattern)
  return(sum(genes_with_pattern))
}

# Define target patterns
patterns <- c(
  "Phospho@\\d+=\\d+;",                           # One certain value
  "Phospho@\\d+=\\d+;Phospho@\\d+=\\d+;",         # Two certain values
  "Phospho@\\d+\\|\\d+;",                         # One uncertain value
  "Phospho@\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+;",                  # Two uncertain values
  "Phospho@\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+;",           # Three uncertain values
  "Phospho@\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+;",    # Four uncertain values
  "Phospho@\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+;",  # Five uncertain values
  "Phospho@\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+\\|\\d+;"  # Six uncertain values
)

# Calculate counts for each pattern
counts <- sapply(patterns, count_genes_with_pattern)

# Prepare data for plotting
plot_data <- data.frame(
  Pattern = c(
    "One Certain Value", "Two Certain Values", 
    "One Uncertain Value", "Two Uncertain Values", 
    "Three Uncertain Values", "Four Uncertain Values", 
    "Five Uncertain Values", "Six Uncertain Values"
  ),
  Count = counts,
  Type = c(
    "Certain", "Certain", 
    "Uncertain", "Uncertain", 
    "Uncertain", "Uncertain", 
    "Uncertain", "Uncertain"
  )
)

# Set colors for the plot
colors <- c("Certain" = "purple", "Uncertain" = "green")

# Plot the bar graph
ggplot(plot_data, aes(x = reorder(Pattern, Count), y = Count, fill = Type)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  scale_fill_manual(values = colors) +
  labs(x = "Phospho Patterns", y = "Number of Genes", title = "Counts of Genes with Different Phospho Patterns") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))  # Optional: for better readability of x-axis labels

EG1 to LG1 phase For ERK1

its effectively analyzes and visualizes phosphorylation changes in the ERK signaling pathway genes during the transition from early G1 (eG1) to late G1 (LG1) phases of the cell cycle.

in the plot, each dot represents a specific measurement of phosphorylation levels at a particular site on the Mapk1”, “Mapk3”, “Raf1”, “Braf”, “Map2k1”, “Map2k2” protein during different phases of the cell cycle (early G1 and late G1), etc..

Each facet of the plot corresponds to a different protine (e.g., BRAF, MAP2K2). This means we can directly compare how phosphorylation levels of each specific protine change across the phases.

The y-axis value of each dot indicates the level of phosphorylation for that site. A higher value suggests more phosphorylation at that site, which can be interpreted as higher activation or activity at that particular phosphorylation site.

The protine present in our dataset are Braf, Map2k2, and Raf1, which matches ERK signaling protine of interest.

# Load necessary libraries
library(reshape2) # For melt function
library(ggplot2) # For ggplot2

# Load the data
data <- read.csv("C:/Users/avani/Downloads/Updated_Data_Mutated-June24.csv")

# Define ERK signaling genes of interest
erk_signaling_genes <- c("Mapk1", "Mapk3", "Raf1", "Braf", "Map2k1", "Map2k2")

# Extract phosphorylation data for ERK signaling genes
phospho_data_erk <- data[data$Gene %in% erk_signaling_genes, ]

# Define the phases of interest (eG1 to LG1)
phases_of_interest <- c("phase_earlyG1_A", "phase_earlyG1_B", "phase_earlyG1_C", 
                        "phase_lateG1_A", "phase_lateG1_B", "phase_lateG1_C")

# Prepare the data for plotting
phospho_data_long_erk <- melt(phospho_data_erk, 
                               id.vars = c("Gene", "New_Gene_Residue"), 
                               measure.vars = phases_of_interest,
                               variable.name = "Phase", value.name = "Phosphorylation")

# Create a new column to categorize phases into eG1 and LG1
phospho_data_long_erk$PhaseCategory <- ifelse(grepl("earlyG1", phospho_data_long_erk$Phase), "eG1", 
                                               ifelse(grepl("lateG1", phospho_data_long_erk$Phase), "LG1", NA))

# Handle missing values by imputing with column means
phospho_data_long_erk$Phosphorylation[is.na(phospho_data_long_erk$Phosphorylation)] <- 
  ave(phospho_data_long_erk$Phosphorylation, phospho_data_long_erk$Phase, FUN = function(x) mean(x, na.rm = TRUE))

# Check the PhaseCategory column and filter out NA values
table(phospho_data_long_erk$PhaseCategory)
## 
## eG1 LG1 
##  12  12
phospho_data_long_erk <- phospho_data_long_erk[!is.na(phospho_data_long_erk$PhaseCategory), ]

# Plot phosphorylation changes for ERK signaling
ggplot(phospho_data_long_erk, aes(x = Phase, y = Phosphorylation, color = PhaseCategory)) +
  geom_point(size = 3) +
  facet_wrap(~ Gene, scales = "free_y") +
  labs(title = "Phosphorylation Changes in ERK Signaling Pathway (eG1 to LG1 Phase)",
       x = "Cell Cycle Phase",
       y = "Phosphorylation Level") +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("eG1" = "purple", "LG1" = "green")) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1),
        legend.position = "bottom")

# Function to print phosphorylation sites and their levels for each gene
print_gene_phospho_sites <- function(gene) {
  gene_data <- phospho_data_long_erk[phospho_data_long_erk$Gene == gene, ]
  gene_sites <- unique(gene_data$New_Gene_Residue)
  
  cat("Number of unique phosphorylation sites for", gene, ":", length(gene_sites), "\n")
  cat("Phosphorylation sites for", gene, ":\n")
  print(gene_sites)
  
  cat("Phosphorylation levels by phase for", gene, ":\n")
  print(gene_data)
  cat("\n\n")
}

# Print phosphorylation sites and their levels for each ERK signaling gene
for (gene in erk_signaling_genes) {
  print_gene_phospho_sites(gene)
}

# Function to print phosphorylation sites and their levels for each gene
print_gene_phospho_sites <- function(gene) {
  gene_data <- phospho_data_long[phospho_data_long$Gene == gene, ]
  gene_sites <- unique(gene_data$New_Gene_Residue)
  
  cat("Number of unique phosphorylation sites for", gene, ":", length(gene_sites), "\n")
  cat("Phosphorylation sites for", gene, ":\n")
  print(gene_sites)
  
  cat("Phosphorylation levels by phase for", gene, ":\n")
  print(gene_data)
  cat("\n\n")
}

  print_gene_phospho_sites(gene)
}

# If the data frame is empty, stop here and print a message
if (nrow(phospho_data_wnt) == 0) {
  stop("No data found for the specified WNT signaling genes.")
}

# Define the phases of interest (lG1 to S)
phases_of_interest <- c("phase_lateG1_A", "phase_lateG1_B", "phase_lateG1_C", 
                        "phase_S_A", "phase_S_B", "phase_S_C")

# Prepare the data for heatmap
phospho_data_wide_wnt <- phospho_data_wnt[, c("Gene", "New_Gene_Residue", phases_of_interest)]
phospho_matrix_wnt <- as.matrix(phospho_data_wide_wnt[,-(1:2)])
rownames(phospho_matrix_wnt) <- paste(phospho_data_wide_wnt$Gene, phospho_data_wide_wnt$New_Gene_Residue, sep = "_")

# Create a heatmap for WNT signaling genes
Heatmap(
  phospho_matrix_wnt, 
  name = "Phosphorylation",
  cluster_rows = TRUE,
  cluster_columns = TRUE,
  show_row_names = TRUE,
  show_column_names = TRUE,
  column_title = "Cell Cycle Phase",
  row_title = "Gene and Residue",
  color = colorRamp2(c(min(phospho_matrix_wnt, na.rm = TRUE), 0, max(phospho_matrix_wnt, na.rm = TRUE)), c("blue", "white", "red"))
)

# Prepare the data for plotting
phospho_data_long_wnt <- melt(phospho_data_wnt, 
                              id.vars = c("Gene", "New_Gene_Residue"), 
                              measure.vars = phases_of_interest,
                              variable.name = "Phase", value.name = "Phospho_Values")

# Check the melted data
print(phospho_data_long_wnt)

# If the data frame is empty, stop here and print a message
if (nrow(phospho_data_wnt) == 0) {
  stop("No data found for the specified WNT signaling genes.")
}

# Define the phases of interest (M to LG1)
phases_of_interest <- c("phase_M_A", "phase_M_B", "phase_M_C", 
                        "phase_lateG1_A", "phase_lateG1_B", "phase_lateG1_C")

# Prepare the data for heatmap
phospho_data_wide_wnt <- phospho_data_wnt[, c("Gene", "New_Gene_Residue", phases_of_interest)]
phospho_matrix_wnt <- as.matrix(phospho_data_wide_wnt[,-(1:2)])
rownames(phospho_matrix_wnt) <- paste(phospho_data_wide_wnt$Gene, phospho_data_wide_wnt$New_Gene_Residue, sep = "_")

# Create a heatmap for WNT signaling genes
Heatmap(
  phospho_matrix_wnt, 
  name = "Phosphorylation",
  cluster_rows = TRUE,
  cluster_columns = TRUE,
  show_row_names = TRUE,
  show_column_names = TRUE,
  column_title = "Cell Cycle Phase",
  row_title = "Gene and Residue",
  color = colorRamp2(c(min(phospho_matrix_wnt, na.rm = TRUE), 0, max(phospho_matrix_wnt, na.rm = TRUE)), c("blue", "white", "red"))
)

# Prepare the data for plotting
phospho_data_long_wnt <- melt(phospho_data_wnt, 
                              id.vars = c("Gene", "New_Gene_Residue"), 
                              measure.vars = phases_of_interest,
                              variable.name = "Phase", value.name = "Phospho_Values")

  stop("No data found for the specified WNT signaling genes.")

# Define all phases of interest
phases_of_interest <- c("phase_earlyG1_A", "phase_earlyG1_B", "phase_earlyG1_C", 
                        "phase_lateG1_A", "phase_lateG1_B", "phase_lateG1_C",
                        "phase_S_A", "phase_S_B", "phase_S_C",
                        "phase_G2_A", "phase_G2_B", "phase_G2_C",
                        "phase_M_A", "phase_M_B", "phase_M_C")

# Prepare the data for heatmap
phospho_data_wide_wnt <- phospho_data_wnt[, c("Gene", "New_Gene_Residue", phases_of_interest)]
phospho_matrix_wnt <- as.matrix(phospho_data_wide_wnt[,-(1:2)])
rownames(phospho_matrix_wnt) <- paste(phospho_data_wide_wnt$Gene, phospho_data_wide_wnt$New_Gene_Residue, sep = "_")

# Create a heatmap for WNT signaling genes
Heatmap(
  phospho_matrix_wnt, 
  name = "Phosphorylation",
  cluster_rows = TRUE,
  cluster_columns = TRUE,
  show_row_names = TRUE,
  show_column_names = TRUE,
  column_title = "Cell Cycle Phase",
  row_title = "Gene and Residue",
  color = colorRamp2(c(min(phospho_matrix_wnt, na.rm = TRUE), 0, max(phospho_matrix_wnt, na.rm = TRUE)), c("blue", "white", "red"))
)

# Prepare the data for plotting
phospho_data_long_wnt <- melt(phospho_data_wnt, 
                              id.vars = c("Gene", "New_Gene_Residue"), 
                              measure.vars = phases_of_interest,
                              variable.name = "Phase", value.name = "Phospho_Values")

# Create a new column to categorize phases
phospho_data_long_wnt$PhaseCategory <- ifelse(grepl("earlyG1", phospho_data_long_wnt$Phase), "earlyG1",
                                              ifelse(grepl("lateG1", phospho_data_long_wnt$Phase), "lateG1",
                                                     ifelse(grepl("S", phospho_data_long_wnt$Phase), "S",
                                                            ifelse(grepl("G2", phospho_data_long_wnt$Phase), "G2",
                                                                   ifelse(grepl("M", phospho_data_long_wnt$Phase), "M", NA)))))

# Handle missing values by imputing with column means
phospho_data_long_wnt$Phospho_Values[is.na(phospho_data_long_wnt$Phospho_Values)] <- 
  ave(phospho_data_long_wnt$Phospho_Values, phospho_data_long_wnt$Phase, FUN = function(x) mean(x, na.rm = TRUE))

# Plot phosphorylation changes for WNT signaling
ggplot(phospho_data_long_wnt, aes(y = Phase, x = Phospho_Values, color = PhaseCategory)) +
  geom_point(size = 3) +
  facet_wrap(~ Gene, scales = "free_x") +
  labs(title = "Phosphorylation Changes in WNT Signaling Pathway (All Phases)",
       y = "Cell Cycle Phase",
       x = "Phosphorylation Level") +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("earlyG1" = "blue", "lateG1" = "green", "S" = "red", "G2" = "purple", "M" = "orange")) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.y = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1),
        legend.position = "right")

# Function to print phosphorylation sites and their levels for each gene
print_gene_phospho_sites <- function(gene) {
  gene_data <- phospho_data_long_wnt[phospho_data_long_wnt$Gene == gene, ]
  gene_sites <- unique(gene_data$New_Gene_Residue)
  
  cat("Number of unique phosphorylation sites for", gene, ":", length(gene_sites), "\n")
  cat("Phosphorylation sites for", gene, ":\n")
  print(gene_sites)
  
  cat("Phosphorylation levels by phase for", gene, ":\n")
  print(gene_data)
  cat("\n\n")
}

# Print phosphorylation sites and their levels for each WNT signaling gene
for (gene in wnt_signaling_genes) {
  print_gene_phospho_sites(gene)
}
